<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2825] Scans respect row locks</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2825</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the javadoc Package org.apache.hadoop.hbase.client Description it states that &quot;Scans (currently) operate without respect for row locks.&quot; I think that since 0.20.4 and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2248&quot; title=&quot;Provide new non-copy mechanism to assure atomic reads in get and scan&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2248&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2248&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; this is no longer the case.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12468934">HBASE-2825</key>
            <summary>Scans respect row locks</summary>
