                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12887986" author="stack" created="Tue, 13 Jul 2010 20:30:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bringing into 0.90.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12905265" author="stack" created="Wed, 1 Sep 2010 22:22:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you make a patch for the javadoc so we can close this Ryan? You know how to say it best!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12905278" author="streamy" created="Wed, 1 Sep 2010 22:35:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Wait, scans respect row locks?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12905279" author="streamy" created="Wed, 1 Sep 2010 22:35:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;(i don&apos;t see that as being the same as providing isolation to concurrent writes)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12905290" author="ryanobjc" created="Wed, 1 Sep 2010 22:49:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;of course not, no read should &apos;respect&apos; a row lock.  Huge performance hit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is just fixing the javadoc, removing that terrible &apos;respect row lock&apos; language&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12905297" author="streamy" created="Wed, 1 Sep 2010 22:57:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So even single-row gets do not use the row lock now?  This is a change in semantics that should be documented if so.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12917082" author="ryanobjc" created="Fri, 1 Oct 2010 22:46:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;tweaked javadoc&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15016854" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:41:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
